text:
Transgender children in Texas and Florida should not be made to fear who they are.

And transgender women of color should not have to fear for their lives.

We must fight for a future where all people can live without fear.

text: June is National Immigrant Heritage Month. As the proud daughter of two immigrants to this country, I know the power of the dreams and aspirations so many have in coming to the United States. Let us continue to celebrate the history and contributions of our immigrant communities.

text: When talking about Roe v. Wade, we need to discuss the right to self-determination: the ability of an individual to make their own decisions about their life and future.

text: The premise and power of Roe v. Wade is that people should have the right to make decisions about their own bodies.

text:
The American Rescue Plan resulted in: 

—Americans getting vaccinated
—Small businesses staying open
—Schools reopening
—Support for frontline workers
—Parents returning to work

But there's still work ahead to keep delivering for all Americans.

text:
Lives are lost to gun violence on streets across America every day. It’s past time to do something.

Ban assault weapons. Expand background checks. Repeal the liability that protects gun manufacturers.

Let’s get this done.

text:
No 86-year-old should fear for her safety when going to the grocery store.  

No nine-year-old should be afraid to go to school.  

No 18-year-old should be able to buy a weapon of war.  
 
We need to pass commonsense gun safety laws.

text:
There’s a through-line from what happened at Tops Market in Buffalo to what happened in Atlanta, in Orlando, and at the Tree of Life synagogue in Pittsburgh. 

There’s no place for hate in our nation.

We must stand up and say: Enough is enough.

text:
The latest jobs report:

390,000 jobs were added last month. 
Nearly 9 million new jobs have been added since taking office.
Historic rates of small business creation.

There’s still more work to do, but we are seeing a shift from recovery to sustainable growth.

text: If the Supreme Court overturns Roe, abortion could be banned in states across the country, putting women’s lives at risk.\n\nSince day one, our position has been clear: We will defend women’s constitutional rights and fight to protect the fundamental right to self-determination.

text:
President @JoeBiden has taken more executive action to combat gun violence than any other president at this point in their administration. 

But we cannot address this alone. 

No more excuses. Thoughts and prayers are important but not enough. We need Congress to act.

text:
At its core, Roe v. Wade recognizes the fundamental right to privacy. 

When the right to privacy is attacked, anyone in our country may face a future where the government can interfere in their personal decisions. 

Not just women. Anyone.

text: Many women—and, in particular Black women—in America, are dealing with this maternal health crisis every day. \n\nThat is why President Joe Biden and I have waged this fight from the White House, treating it as a national priority. https://t.co/9gNcIp0WhX

text: Our nation is facing a maternal health crisis.\n\nWhen women do not get the health care they need, families, communities, and our nation suffer. That is why we are taking action to make sure that mothers in our country have the care they need to thrive.

text: Many of America’s children are breathing polluted air on their way to school.\n\nThe Bipartisan Infrastructure Law will start to replace diesel school buses with clean electric buses. Together, we can protect our children's health, address the climate crisis, and grow our economy.

I sat down with the next generation of leaders to hear what Earth Day means to them. https://t.co/FnmtXitUnV

text: Last year, we made a historic investment in our nation’s infrastructure when we passed the Bipartisan Infrastructure Law.\n\nIt'll put thousands of union workers, sheet metal workers, carpenters, pipefitters, and plumbers to work across the country to modernize our infrastructure.

text: The American Rescue Plan invested more than $60 billion to help our nation’s small businesses recover from the pandemic.\n\nRoughly half of America’s workers either work for or run a small business. This funding has been critical to our recovery.

text: Through the Bipartisan Infrastructure Law, historic investments are being made to our infrastructure and supply chains to prevent bottlenecks and lower daily expenses. \n\nWe are working towards lowering costs for families while creating good-paying jobs.

text: We can address the climate crisis, protect the health of our children, connect our communities to reliable and accessible public transportation, and grow our economy at the same time.\n\nThanks to funding from the Bipartisan Infrastructure Law, we are working to do just that.

text: As my mother always used to say, “You may be the first to do many things, but make sure you are not the last.”\n\nOn International Women’s Day, we recognize how far women have come—and how far we have to go to achieve full equality and representation.

The bottom line is that eliminating lead exposure in our nation must be among our highest priorities.

Why? Because millions of people in America are exposed to lead every day.

Our Lead Pipe and Paint Action Plan will remove and replace all lead pipes over the next ten years.

text: Pregnant women who live in rural communities are about 60% more likely to die before, during, or after childbirth.\n\nWe’re facing a maternal health crisis, and President Biden and I are treating it as a matter of public health.

text: Today, we honor the six million Jews and other victims murdered by the Nazi regime during the Holocaust. We must teach our children the truth about the atrocities of the Holocaust, so that together we give meaning to that timeless pledge: “never again.”

text: From adding 6 million new jobs to the unemployment rate dropping to 3.9%, last year was a year of enormous progress.\n\nWe’re getting America’s economy back on track.

text:
In our first year in office:

—More than 6 million jobs created 
—The unemployment rate is down to 3.9%
—Unemployment claims are at their lowest level since 1969

We’re making historic progress for workers, small businesses, and our economy—and it’s only just the beginning.

text: Today, President Biden announced that we are in the process of purchasing an additional 500 million more tests to meet future demand. \n\nThe American people will now have more access to convenient COVID-19 at-home tests.

text: Like so many others, I stand on the shoulders of giants like Congressman John Lewis and remind myself of the work we have left to do. Democracy is stronger when everyone participates—and is weaker when people are left out.

text: Years from now, our children and grandchildren will ask us what we did at this moment in history.\n\nThe U.S. Senate must act with the urgency this moment demands and safeguard our democracy for generations to come. https://t.co/8abqBXw03c

text: The John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act and the Freedom to Vote Act represent the first real opportunity to secure the freedom to vote since the Supreme Court gutted the Voting Rights Act.\n\nWe don't know when we'll have this opportunity again—the Senate must act now.
context_annotations: [{"domain": {"id": "10", "name": "Person", "description": "Named people in the world like Nelson Mandela"}, "entity": {"id": "875006493984149509", "name": "Kamala Harris", "description": "US Senator Kamala Harris (CA)"}}, {"domain": {"id": "35", "name": "Politician", "description": "Politicians in the world, like Joe Biden"}, "entity": {"id": "875006493984149509", "name": "Kamala Harris", "description": "US Senator Kamala Harris (CA)"}}]

text: Make no mistake: There is nothing normal about laws that prevent the American people from exercising their constitutional right to vote. \n\nTwo landmark voting rights bills sit before the Senate. The Senate must act to protect the will of the people. https://t.co/ijeYvXGiZF
context_annotations: [{"domain": {"id": "10", "name": "Person", "description": "Named people in the world like Nelson Mandela"}, "entity": {"id": "875006493984149509", "name": "Kamala Harris", "description": "US Senator Kamala Harris (CA)"}}, {"domain": {"id": "35", "name": "Politician", "description": "Politicians in the world, like Joe Biden"}, "entity": {"id": "875006493984149509", "name": "Kamala Harris", "description": "US Senator Kamala Harris (CA)"}}]

text: We will fight to safeguard our democracy and secure our most fundamental freedom: the freedom to vote. \n\nThe Senate must pass the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act and the Freedom to Vote Act to protect our right to vote.
context_annotations: [{"domain": {"id": "10", "name": "Person", "description": "Named people in the world like Nelson Mandela"}, "entity": {"id": "875006493984149509", "name": "Kamala Harris", "description": "US Senator Kamala Harris (CA)"}}, {"domain": {"id": "35", "name": "Politician", "description": "Politicians in the world, like Joe Biden"}, "entity": {"id": "875006493984149509", "name": "Kamala Harris", "description": "US Senator Kamala Harris (CA)"}}]

geo.name: NA

text: Passing the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act and the Freedom to Vote Act is urgent. These bills represent the first real opportunity for voting rights since the Supreme Court gutted the Voting Rights Act a decade ago. We don't know when we'll have this opportunity again.
context_annotations: [{"domain": {"id": "10", "name": "Person", "description": "Named people in the world like Nelson Mandela"}, "entity": {"id": "875006493984149509", "name": "Kamala Harris", "description": "US Senator Kamala Harris (CA)"}}, {"domain": {"id": "35", "name": "Politician", "description": "Politicians in the world, like Joe Biden"}, "entity": {"id": "875006493984149509", "name": "Kamala Harris", "description": "US Senator Kamala Harris (CA)"}}]

text: Tune in as I deliver remarks on the urgent need to pass legislation to protect the constitutional right to vote and the integrity of our elections. https://t.co/kz4fG9emEN

text: Free and fair elections are central to our democracy. The Senate must pass the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act and the Freedom to Vote Act to protect our right to vote.
context_annotations: [{"domain": {"id": "10", "name": "Person", "description": "Named people in the world like Nelson Mandela"}, "entity": {"id": "875006493984149509", "name": "Kamala Harris", "description": "US Senator Kamala Harris (CA)"}}, {"domain": {"id": "35", "name": "Politician", "description": "Politicians in the world, like Joe Biden"}, "entity": {"id": "875006493984149509", "name": "Kamala Harris", "description": "US Senator Kamala Harris (CA)"}}]

geo.name: NA

text: The Freedom to Vote Act and the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act are about ensuring that all Americans—wherever they live, whatever party they are registered to vote with—have the  ability to exercise their vote.\n\nThe Senate must act to protect this sacred right.
context_annotations: [{"domain": {"id": "10", "name": "Person", "description": "Named people in the world like Nelson Mandela"}, "entity": {"id": "875006493984149509", "name": "Kamala Harris", "description": "US Senator Kamala Harris (CA)"}}, {"domain": {"id": "35", "name": "Politician", "description": "Politicians in the world, like Joe Biden"}, "entity": {"id": "875006493984149509", "name": "Kamala Harris", "description": "US Senator Kamala Harris (CA)"}}]

text: We must protect voting rights. \n\nThat’s why the Senate must pass the Freedom to Vote Act and the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act to ensure that everyone can count on  access to the ballot box. https://t.co/1re8h3gpGa
context_annotations: [{"domain": {"id": "10", "name": "Person", "description": "Named people in the world like Nelson Mandela"}, "entity": {"id": "875006493984149509", "name": "Kamala Harris", "description": "US Senator Kamala Harris (CA)"}}, {"domain": {"id": "35", "name": "Politician", "description": "Politicians in the world, like Joe Biden"}, "entity": {"id": "875006493984149509", "name": "Kamala Harris", "description": "US Senator Kamala Harris (CA)"}}]

text: Our democracy is being threatened by an attack on voting rights. \n\nWe must fight to save our democracy by fighting for the right for all people, whoever they vote for, to vote.
context_annotations: [{"domain": {"id": "10", "name": "Person", "description": "Named people in the world like Nelson Mandela"}, "entity": {"id": "875006493984149509", "name": "Kamala Harris", "description": "US Senator Kamala Harris (CA)"}}, {"domain": {"id": "35", "name": "Politician", "description": "Politicians in the world, like Joe Biden"}, "entity": {"id": "875006493984149509", "name": "Kamala Harris", "description": "US Senator Kamala Harris (CA)"}}]

geo.name: NA

text: For the sake of one of the most important pillars of our democracy, we must put politics aside, step up, and act. \n\nThe Senate must pass the Freedom to Vote Act and the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act.
context_annotations: [{"domain": {"id": "10", "name": "Person", "description": "Named people in the world like Nelson Mandela"}, "entity": {"id": "875006493984149509", "name": "Kamala Harris", "description": "US Senator Kamala Harris (CA)"}}, {"domain": {"id": "35", "name": "Politician", "description": "Politicians in the world, like Joe Biden"}, "entity": {"id": "875006493984149509", "name": "Kamala Harris", "description": "US Senator Kamala Harris (CA)"}}, {"domain": {"id": "152", "name": "Food", "description": "Topics about food, like Donuts or Brunch"}, "entity": {"id": "1303483003801202688", "name": "Sake"}}]

text: Activists and leaders including Dr. Martin Luther King, John Lewis, and Rosa Parks have fought to expand voting rights. \n\nWe owe it to future generations to continue to fight for every American’s right to vote and have their vote counted.

text: The unemployment rate fell to 3.9%—the sharpest one-year drop in unemployment on record. \n\nWe’re making progress for workers, small businesses, and our economy.

text: Sidney Poitier transformed our world both on and off the screen. As an Oscar-winning actor and Ambassador, he advanced our dialogue on race and civil rights at a time when we needed it most. My thoughts are with his wife Joanna and his daughters.

text: States across our nation have passed laws that would make it harder to vote.\n\nWe are in a critical moment, and that is why we must pass the Freedom to Vote Act and the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act. It will not be easy, but we must fight back.

text: What was at stake on January 6, and now, is the right to have our future decided the way the Constitution prescribes it: By We, the People. All the people. https://t.co/a6c4LHn1Qh

text:
Today’s jobs report: 

—Added 6.4 million jobs since January of last year 
—Lowest unemployment rate since the beginning of the pandemic
—Regained 84% of jobs lost in the pandemic 

Today is a historic day of our economic recovery as Americans are getting back to work.

text: How will January 6 be remembered in the years ahead?\n\nThe American spirit is being tested and the answer to whether we will meet that test resides where it always has resided in our country, with you, the people. https://t.co/XtIhwDFoEe

text:
January 6 reflects the dual nature of democracy—its fragility and strength. 

The fragility of democracy is that if we are not vigilant, democracy will not stand.

The strength of democracy is that everyone should be treated equally and that elections should be free and fair.

text:
Our Build Back Better Act invests in maternal health care by:

-Extending mandatory postpartum Medicaid coverage
-Investing in the maternal, prenatal, and postpartum workforce
-Improving maternal mental health
-Supporting community-based programs

We must act.

Black women are more than 3x as likely to die from pregnancy-related complications. 

Native American women are more than 2x as likely to die.

Women in rural America are about 60% more likely to die.

Our Build Back Better Act will do something about that.

He is an American hero. https://t.co/Uni30Lb18x

1️⃣ Building our STEM workforce 
2️⃣ Addressing the climate crisis
3️⃣ Promoting rules and norms that govern space

These will guide our work as we venture through space exploration.

— Lower child care costs

text:
The Build Back Better Framework is a win for all Americans:

Universal pre-K.
Tax cuts for the middle class.
Lower health care costs.
An unprecedented effort to combat climate change.

text: We can build an economy that gives working people a fair shot, restores fairness to our tax code, and makes crucial investments that we need to fight climate change. \n\nWe need to pass our Build Back Better Agenda and the Bipartisan Infrastructure Deal.

text: We have an opportunity to prove to the American people that their government works for them—not just those at the top. \n\nWe must deliver by passing the Build Back Better Agenda and the Bipartisan Infrastructure Deal.

text:
Our Build Back Better Agenda will lower health care costs, reduce the cost of child care, cut taxes for the middle class, and make big investments to fight climate change. 

How will we pay for it?

By making the ultra-wealthy and large corporations pay their fair share.

text: President @JoeBiden believes we face an urgent choice: do we keep an economy that serves the wealthiest and biggest corporations? Or do we finally give middle-class families a fair shot?\n\nThe answer is simple: it’s time to uplift America's working families.

text: The Build Back Better Agenda is our opportunity to prove to the American people that their government works for them—not just those at the top.

text: For a long time, this economy has worked great for those at the top while working families have been cut out of the deal. \n\nOur Build Back Better Agenda will deliver economic growth that works for everyone.

text: We can build an economy that gives working people a fair shot, restore fairness to our tax code, and make crucial investments that we need to fight climate change. \n\nWe need to pass our Build Back Better Agenda.

text: Our Build Back Better Agenda will cut taxes for the middle class, lower costs for working families, create jobs, and sustain economic growth for years to come.

text: The ultra-wealthy and corporations don’t need another tax cut.\n\nYou know who does? The middle class.

text: Instead of continuing to fight the wars of the past, we must answer the challenges of our collective future. America will lead the world to a more peaceful and prosperous future for all of us. https://t.co/S3D1SH31UD

text: Our Build Back Better Agenda is built on the belief that a strong economy depends on a solid foundation of public investment—and that today’s investments in workers, families, and communities will pay dividends for generations to come.
context_annotations: [{"domain": {"id": "10", "name": "Person", "description": "Named people in the world like Nelson Mandela"}, "entity": {"id": "875006493984149509", "name": "Kamala Harris", "description": "US Senator Kamala Harris (CA)"}}, {"domain": {"id": "35", "name": "Politician", "description": "Politicians in the world, like Joe Biden"}, "entity": {"id": "875006493984149509", "name": "Kamala Harris", "description": "US Senator Kamala Harris (CA)"}}]

text: For decades, Republicans have fought to cut taxes for the ultra-wealthy, all while underinvesting in public goods like infrastructure and innovation.\n\nOur Build Back Better Agenda will lower costs for middle-class families. When the middle class does better, everyone does better.
context_annotations: [{"domain": {"id": "10", "name": "Person", "description": "Named people in the world like Nelson Mandela"}, "entity": {"id": "875006493984149509", "name": "Kamala Harris", "description": "US Senator Kamala Harris (CA)"}}, {"domain": {"id": "35", "name": "Politician", "description": "Politicians in the world, like Joe Biden"}, "entity": {"id": "875006493984149509", "name": "Kamala Harris", "description": "US Senator Kamala Harris (CA)"}}]

author.description: Fighting for the people. Wife, Momala, Auntie. She/her. Official account is @VP.
geo.name: NA

text: So-called “trickle-down” economics never worked for working families. \n\nOur Build Back Better Agenda will invest in the middle class and have the ultra-wealthy and corporations pay their fair share.
context_annotations: [{"domain": {"id": "10", "name": "Person", "description": "Named people in the world like Nelson Mandela"}, "entity": {"id": "875006493984149509", "name": "Kamala Harris", "description": "US Senator Kamala Harris (CA)"}}, {"domain": {"id": "35", "name": "Politician", "description": "Politicians in the world, like Joe Biden"}, "entity": {"id": "875006493984149509", "name": "Kamala Harris", "description": "US Senator Kamala Harris (CA)"}}]

geo.name: NA

text: If big corporations and the very wealthy pay their fair share, we can invest in the American people, cut taxes for the middle class, reduce health care costs, create jobs, fight climate change, and so much more. https://t.co/4U1XeNqe2V

text:
We went to Afghanistan almost 20 years ago with clear goals: get those who attacked us on September 11, 2001—and make sure al Qaeda could not use Afghanistan as a base from which to attack us again.

We did that—a decade ago.

Our mission was never supposed to be nation building.

In the 21st century, broadband is a critical infrastructure.

text: Today is a historic day. Senate Democrats and Republicans came together to pass the Bipartisan Infrastructure Deal.\n \nIt will put people to work in good-paying jobs expanding broadband to every community, fixing lead pipes, building electric school buses, and more.

Nineteen Republicans joined all 50 Democrats to pass the bill. The bill will now go to the House of Representatives.

Major spending areas in the plan include:

- The legislation adds $550 billion to what Congress was already planning to spend on infrastructure over the next eight years
- $110 billion would go to roads, bridges and major projects
- $66 billion to passenger and freight rail
- $65 billion for expanded broadband internet access
- $39 billion to improve transit systems
- $55 billion for water infrastructure, including a plan to replace lead pipes
- $7.5 billion to create a national charging infrastructure for electric vehicles"}}]

text: The right to vote is the right that unlocks all other rights. When we cast a ballot, we decide our leaders. When we cast a ballot, we determine our future.\n\nCongress must pass the For the People Act and the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act to protect our sacred right.

text: Folks, the Delta variant — a highly infectious COVID-19 strain — is spreading rapidly among young people between 12 and 20 years old in the U.K. If you’re young and haven’t gotten your shot yet, it really is time. It’s the best way to protect yourself and those you love.

text: Nearly 10 million Americans are still unemployed. With a once-in-a-generation investment in our country’s infrastructure, the American Jobs Plan will put our nation back to work.

We can ban assault weapons and high-capacity magazines.
 
We can close loopholes in our gun background check system.
 
This is not a partisan issue — it’s an American issue that will save lives. Congress needs to act.

text:
The American Rescue Plan is getting:

- America vaccinated
- $1,400 checks to those in need
- At least a $3,000 tax credit per child to parents
- Unemployment benefits extended for 11 million Americans

In short, it's giving Americans the help they need to get through COVID.

text:
In two months, we’ve:

- Passed the American Rescue Plan
- Administered 100 million shots
- Rejoined the Paris Agreement
- Reversed the transgender military and Muslim bans
- Expanded access to health care and voting
- Acted to end private prisons

And we're just getting started.

Last week, the Biden-Harris Administration:

- Reached 50 million vaccinations
- Announced the shipment of 25 million masks
- Increased weekly vaccine supply to 14.5 million doses
- Opened vaccination sites across the country

We’re working hard to beat COVID-19.

text:

This coming week, our Administration will likely administer over 12 million shots.

That’s double the pace in just six weeks.

text:
Starting this week, our Administration is:

- Increasing weekly vaccine shipments to states to 13.5 million doses — a 57% increase from when I took office.
- Doubling our direct shipments to local pharmacies.

We’re working hard to get America vaccinated quickly.

text:
People in this country are hurting right now – especially women. About 2.5 million women have lost their jobs or dropped out of the workforce during the pandemic.

The American Rescue Plan addresses these urgent challenges.
 
It's time for Congress to act.

text:
My abiding hope—my abiding prayer—is that we emerge from this ordeal with a new wisdom.

To cherish simple moments. 
To imagine new possibilities. 

And to open our hearts just a little more to one another.
